ment of 60 years of age.This is a voluntary contribution scheme for traders, retailers, small shopkeepers.Central govt. will also pay equal amount of contribution.The monthly contribution amount will be Rs. 55 to Rs. 200 depending on the age of applicant.The pension amount would be provided through Life Insurance Corporation (LIC) of India.So to avail benefits of this pension scheme, all the vyaparis are advised to fill the form at nearest CSCs as soon as possible. All the small shopkeepers and retail traders with annual turnover less than Rs. 1.5 crore would be its beneficiaries.Eligibility for National Pension Scheme for Traders and Self Employed Persons YojanaThe eligibility criteria for PM Karam Yogi Maandhan Yojana is described below:- \u2014 Only the traders in the age group of 18 to 40 years are eligible. \u2014 The applicant must not be an existing beneficiary of EPFO, ESIC, NPS, PM-SYM schemes or an income tax payee.National Pension Scheme for Traders and Self Employed Persons Yojana is a government scheme meant for old age protection and social security of Shopkeeper\u2019s, Retail traders and Self Employed persons.PM Laghu Vyapaari Mandhan Yojna \u2013 References\u2014 In case of any query, applicants can call on toll free number at 1800 267 6888 or can send an e-mail at  vyapari@gov.in or shramyogi@gov.in. \u2014 For more details, visit the official website at https://maandhan.in/vyapari  Sarkari Yojana App - Download Now Source / Reference Link: https://maandhan.in/  at  "}